242	| Breathing card | `'$name breathing exercise, $duration, $difficulty, tap to start'` |
243	| Stretching card | `'$name stretching routine, $duration, tap to view guide'` |
244	| Difficulty badge | `'$difficulty level'` |
245	| Trimester badge | `'$suitability trimester suitability'` |
246	
247	### Focus Order
248	
249	1. AppBar (back button)
250	2. Breathing exercises section header
251	3. Breathing exercise cards (top to bottom)
252	4. Stretching section header
253	5. Stretching routine cards (top to bottom)
254	
255	### Contrast Notes
256	
257	- All text meets WCAG AA contrast (4.5:1 minimum)
258	- `deepGraphite` on `morningMist`: ~12:1
259	- `stoneGrey` on `morningMist`: ~4.7:1
260	
261	### Screen Reader Support
262	
263	- `ExcludeSemantics` on decorative chevron icons
264	- Live region when overlay is triggered: "Opening $name"
265	
266	---
267	
268	## 11. Anti-Patterns
269	
270	**Do Not:**
271	- Add a FAB to this screen (per UX spec, FAB is None)
272	- Add `BottomNavigationBar` (hidden per spec)
273	- Use platform default colors — all from design system
274	- Use any font other than Nunito
275	- Use pure black (#000000) or pure white (#FFFFFF) for text
276	- Create touch targets smaller than 48dp
277	- Add animations that are abrupt or bouncy — use gentle `easeInOut`
278	- Use gradients on cards — flat `morningMist` only
279	- Add more than two main sections — keep it focused
280	- Use `GridView` — this is a simple vertical list
281	
282	---
283	
284	## 12. Critical Files for Implementation
285	
286	1. **`lib/router/app_router.dart`** — Add GoRoute entry for `/mindfulness` pointing to `MindfulnessScreen`
287	
288	2. **`lib/theme/app_theme.dart`** — Reference for design tokens (spacing, colors, typography scale)
289	
290	3. **`lib/screens/pregnancy_progress/pregnancy_progress_screen.dart`** — Reference implementation pattern for a push-screen with `Scaffold`, `AppBar`, `ListView` body, and card-based content
291	
292	4. **`.stitch/designs/mindfulness/SPEC.md`** — This specification document
293	
294	5. **`.stitch/screens.json`** — Reference for screen definitions and overlay parent relationships (`mindfulness` → `breathing-exercise`, `stretching-guide`)
295	
296	---
297	
298	## 13. Screen Structure
299	
300	```
301	MindfulnessScreen
302	├── Scaffold
303	│   ├── AppBar ("Mindfulness", back button)
304	│   └── body: ListView
305	│       ├── Section 1: Breathing Exercises
306	│       │   └── ListView.separated
307	│       │       └── BreathingExerciseCard × N
308	│       └── Section 2: Stretching & Self-Care
309	│           └── ListView.separated
310	│               └── StretchingRoutineCard × N
311	```
312	
313	---
314	
315	## 14. Route Definition
316	
317	```dart
318	GoRoute(
319	  path: '/mindfulness',
320	  builder: (context, state) => const MindfulnessScreen(),
321	),
322	```
323	
324	---
325	
326	## 15. Overlay Handling
327	
328	The breathing exercise and stretching guide overlays are separate routes (`overlay:breathing-exercise`, `overlay:stretching-guide`). For MVP, these can be implemented as:
329	
330	- `BreathingExerciseOverlay` (full-screen, pushes over navigation stack)
331	- `StretchingGuideSheet` (bottom sheet, uses `showModalBottomSheet`)
